name: Preliminary Activities and Materials Approval Checklist
All Technical Query Forms (TQs) Reviewed and Approved for Works
S50 Concrete Mix Design Approved by Client
S65 Concrete Mix Design Approved by Client
S65 Xypex Concrete Mix Design Approved by Client
Inspection of Delivery to Confirm Compliance with Order and Drawings
Cut Bar Length Tolerance +0mm -10mm, Bends in Plane, Correct Cog Lengths etc.
Inspection of Delivery for Completeness and Quality
Inspection of Delivery for Completeness and Quality
Mould Dimensions are within Shop Drawings Tolerance
Detailed inspection of Mould and cage
All Lifting Inserts are installed in accordance with Drawings
All ferrules installed in accordance with Drawings
Position of anti-burts reinforcement in accordance to drawings and tolerance table
Ducts position in accordance with drawings
Grout tubes instaled as per drawings (for columns only)
Temporary works ferrules installed as per drawing
(HOLD POINT FOR CLIENT TO SIGN OFF)
Slump within Allowable Tolerance (180+/-40) (Tested 1st truck and subsequently for every 25m3)
Trucks Tested for strength (Tested 1st truck and subsequently for every 25m3)
Time Lag Between Dischard not exceeded 30 minutes
Concrete Placed within allowable time from Batching Plant (90min)
No Free Fall During Pour (not more than 2 metres from ground)
Required Finish Applied as per Drawings
Retarders applied on Green Cut areas as shown in drawings
Curing compound applied to top surface
Concrete Cylinders Crushed and Checked for stripping strength
(HOLD POINT FOR CLIENT TO SIGN OFF)
Application of curing compound to all formed faces of the unit after lbeing lifted from the mould
Lifted and Handled as per Drawings
Storage as per Approved Temporary Works Drawings
Product Dimensions Achieved and are within Specified Tolerance
Cast-in Items are all in Place and within Specified Tolerance
Bottom surface clear from tie wire (Attach Pictures)
Repairs Completed as per approved WMS (if applicable)
NCR Approved by Client and Repairs Completed (if applicable)
As-Built Drawings Completed, Stamped and Attached
